all eased again.","Sibur cut Hai Phong PE offers 400–700 VND/kg.","LLDPE down to 35,500; HDPE 38,300–38,500; LDPE over 50,000 stalled."]},"PVC":{"sub":"Imports cut, domestic flat","bullets":["Formosa slashed July offer to VN to $810–820 CIF.","Carbide SG-5 held 22,000–22,300 for ~10 days.","Oil-based fell to 24,000; only S65 moved domestically."]}},"regional":[{"l":"SEA · HD Film/Yarn","v":"1,310–1,320","d":-30},{"l":"SEA · LL Film","v":"1,270","d":-30},{"l":"SEA · LL C6","v":"1,420","d":-30},{"l":"SEA · LD Film","v":"1,520","d":-30},{"l":"SEA · PP Yarn/Inj","v":"1,240","d":-30},{"l":"SEA · PP BOPP","v":"1,270","d":-20},{"l":"Formosa PVC to VN","v":"810–820","d":-120},{"l":"Cheapest oil PVC to VN","v":"720","d":-90}],"changedNote":"All moved down, mainly PP"},"reports":{"PE":{"summary":["Chinese LDPE Film offers to Vietnam edged slightly lower this week, while LLDPE and HDPE import offers also declined compared with the previous week.","Sibur Russia cut its domestic LLDPE and HDPE offers at Hai Phong port by 400–700 VND/kg, and the overall PE price trend continued falling with wide gaps between suppliers.","Domestic LLDPE settled as low as 35,500 VND/kg and HDPE as low as 38,300–38,500 VND/kg, while LDPE Film offered above 50,000 VND/kg struggled to close any deals."],"paras":["Today, June 9, the import offer price for Sinopec China's LDPE Film 2426H to Vietnam was reported at 1,440 USD/ton CIF; the offer price for ZPC's LDPE Film 2426H/2420H was at 1,430 USD/ton CIF. The import offer price for Exxon – China's LDPE Film 2022.AC and 2022.BW was at 1,455 USD/ton CIF. In the previous week, the offer prices for LDPE Film grades 2426H/2420H from Yulong and Wanhua China were at 1,440–1,470 USD/ton CIF. Thus, the general level of LDPE offers from China this week edged down slightly.","For LLDPE, today one distributor offered Petrochina China's LLDPE Film 7042/7042N to Vietnam at 1,120–1,130 USD/ton CIF, down 25 USD/ton compared with last week's offer. The offer price for Exxon Mobil US's LLDPE Film 2018AY (re-exported from China) to Vietnam was at 1,210 USD/ton CIF.","For HDPE, the offer price for HDPE Film originating from BASF China was at 1,215 USD/ton CIF, and that originating from Baofeng China was at 1,240 USD/ton CIF. In addition, one distributor offered HDPE blow 5502 originating from Tricon US to Vietnam at 1,170 USD/ton CIF, and offered HDPE blow 5502H originating from Cynpol US at 1,190 USD/ton CIF. Overall, offer prices declined over last week.","Domestically, at Hai Phong port, Sibur Russia's distributor today offered LLDPE Film to Vietnam at 34,200 VND/kg including VAT — down 400 VND/kg compared with last week; offered HDPE Film grades at 36,500 VND/kg including VAT — down 500 VND/kg compared with last week; offered HDPE yarn at 35,600 VND/kg including VAT — down 700 VND/kg compared with last week; and HDPE injection at 35,200–35,500 VND/kg including VAT — down 500 VND/kg compared with last week.","In the domestic market, at the start of this week, the PE price trend continued to decline compared with the end of last week. The gap in offer prices between suppliers was quite large.","For example, with LLDPE, Sabic's LLDPE Film 218WJ and Qamar's FD21HS recorded one distributor settling at 35,500 VND/kg including VAT — the lowest in the market; some trading companies settled at 36,000–36,400 VND/kg including VAT; but there were also small trading companies still holding offers up to 37,000 VND/kg including VAT.","For HDPE, Sabic's HDPE Film FJ00952 and Qamar's F1 recorded some sellers offering at 39,500–40,000 VND/kg including VAT; however, one large distributor settled at 38,300–38,500 VND/kg including VAT — the lowest in the market at present.","As for LDPE, the offer prices for LDPE Film grades at this time were generally in the range of 46,000–50,000 VND/kg including VAT; suppliers offering above 50,000 VND/kg including VAT almost failed to reach any deals..."]},"PP":{"summary":["Sabic settled its PP copo selling price at 1,200 USD/ton CIF, 50–60 USD/ton below yesterday's bid, while Chinese-origin PP offers stayed high and uncompetitive.","Domestic and Russian PP homo supply led prices lower, with NSRP and Sibur grades undercutting the market and some sellers settling well below their offers.","Imported grades had to slash prices to sell as buyers shifted to cheaper equivalent products like T3034, and Sabic PP copo settled in the south at 39,000 VND/kg, undercutting domestic producers."],"paras":["Yesterday, June 8, Sabic's distributor announced new bid prices for PP copo and random grades to Vietnamese buyers, with goods from its plant in Saudi Arabia subject to a 3% import tax. Accordingly, the bid prices for Sabic's PP copo grades were at 1,250–1,260 USD/ton CIF, with shipments from Singapore.","Today, June 9, Sabic continued to announce the settled selling price for a PP copo batch from its Saudi Arabian plant, subject to a 3% import tax. The settled price was at 1,200 USD/ton CIF, 50–60 USD/ton lower than the bid price for the batch announced yesterday.","The supply of PP originating from China to Vietnam this week remained fairly abundant and diverse in grades, but the offer prices were assessed as relatively high compared with the general market and not very competitive.","Accordingly, one distributor offered PP yarn/injection, BOPP, and PP Fibre from Oriental and Grand Resource in the range of 1,285–1,310 USD/ton FOB China; specifically, Jinneng's PP yarn HP500J was offered at 1,200 USD/ton FOB Qingdao. Oriental and CNPC's PP block copo was at 1,350–1,355 USD/ton FOB Ningbo. PPR offers from Oriental, Grand Resource, Chambroad, and Sinochem were generally at 1,315–1,360 USD/ton FOB. IPP and CPP from Chambroad and Grand Resource were offered at 1,320–1,360 USD/ton FOB. Typically, the CIF Vietnam price adds about 20–30 USD/ton to the FOB offer prices mentioned above.","Domestically, today, the distributor of Sibur Russia offered PP yarn/injection and non-woven grades to Vietnamese buyers at 33,900–34,300 VND/kg including VAT at Hai Phong port, down sharply by 1,300–1,600 VND/kg compared with last week; PP copo was offered at 34,800 VND/kg including VAT at Hai Phong port, down 700 VND/kg compared with last week.","NSRP's leading distributor, Marubeni, this week is offering NSRP's PP 114G at 34,000 VND/kg including VAT, while many trading companies in the north are also offering PP 114G at 34,000–34,200 VND/kg including VAT depending on quantity. However, the market recorded some sellers who accepted to settle this product at 33,400–33,600 VND/kg including VAT, and buyers purchasing in large quantities could potentially negotiate even better prices.","Thus, for the PP homo line, NSRP's domestic goods and Sibur Russia's goods are being offered at prices cheaper than the market. PP originating from China also recorded some grades offered by sellers at 33,500–33,600 VND/kg including VAT, but the gap in offer prices between suppliers and between grades was still quite large.","BSR's PP T3034 offered for sale in the south or shipped to the north had both dropped to 35,000 VND/kg including VAT, but goods sold in the north were hard to move due to the high price gap compared with NSRP's goods.","In this context, many imported grades, despite low and even scarce ready-delivery inventory, still had to cut prices to meet consumption. A number of sellers reported that the capital cost of Thailand's PP 1102K or Saudi Arabia's new water-route batch was at 40,000–41,000 VND/kg including VAT, but to be consumed they also had to accept settling at only about 37,000–38,000 VND/kg including VAT, because buyers have recently switched to goods of equivalent quality such as T3034 to replace it in order to lower production costs.","Similarly, for PP copo, the market recorded a seller in the south settling Sabic's PP copo at only 39,000 VND/kg including VAT, much lower than PP copo from domestic producers such as Hyosung Vina or LSP (still offered above and below 40,000 VND/kg including VAT).."]},"PVC":{"summary":["Formosa sharply cut its July PVC offer prices across all markets, lowering its offer to Vietnam to 810–820 USD/ton/CIF, while a separate supplier offered LG Chem and Hygain PVC to Vietnamese buyers at an even cheaper 720 USD/ton/CIF.","Domestic carbide-based PVC SG-5 from Yihua and Xinfa held flat at 22,000–22,300 VND/kg including VAT for about 10 days, even as oil-based PVC prices kept declining.","Oil-based Chinese PVC fell to 24,000 VND/kg including VAT and domestic or Thai grades were sold at 24,000–24,500 VND/kg including VAT, with the declines driven by cautious sentiment ahead of the low season."],"paras":["Today, June 9, Formosa announced its PVC offer prices for cargo to be delivered in July 2026. Accordingly, Formosa's PVC offer price to India this month dropped sharply by 115 USD/ton compared with the settlement price of the previous month, falling to 815 USD/ton/CIF; the offer price to China dropped sharply by 120 USD/ton compared with last month's settlement price, falling to 760 USD/ton/CIF. Offer prices to other markets also fell by 120 USD/ton compared with the previous month, calculated at a FOB price of 730 USD/ton/FOB Taiwan, with a volume discount of 10 USD/ton.","In the previous month, Formosa's PVC offer price to Vietnam was at 930–940 USD/ton, and with this month's announced price cut of 120 USD/ton, the offer price falls to 810–820 USD/ton/CIF. Although the FOB price is only at 730 USD/ton/FOB Taiwan, adding shipping costs to Vietnam brings the CIF price for Vietnam to around 770–780 USD/ton/CIF.","In Vietnam, at the end of last week, a supplier offered PVC TL-1000 originating from LG Chem (whose factory is located in China) and PVC HS-1000R under the Hygain brand (produced by Haijing China) to Vietnamese buyers, both at 720 USD/ton/CIF, under EXW conditions (goods delivered at the seller's factory), at a bonded warehouse in Hai Phong, with an import tax of 5%. These offer prices dropped sharply by 70 USD/ton and 110 USD/ton respectively compared with the middle of last month. This is still the cheapest price level for oil-based imported PVC at the present time.","In domestic trading, early this week, the selling offer price for PVC from traders dealing in spot cargo fell slightly compared with the end of last week. The selling price of PVC SG-5 (carbide-based) originating from Yihua and Xinfa China in the northern region is commonly at 22,000–22,300 VND/kg including VAT, a \"bottom\" level that has held flat for about 10 days, despite oil-based PVC prices continuing to decline steadily.","Currently, oil-based PVC originating from China has fallen to a level of 24,000 VND/kg including VAT. PVC SG660/SP660, PM66R originating domestically or from Thailand has also been recorded with some sellers—large commercial traders—accepting settlement at a selling price of 24,000–24,500 VND/kg including VAT, lower than the settlement selling price set by the manufacturer at the end of May. The reason is the very cautious market sentiment as the low season approaches."]}},"generatedAt":"2026-06-10T08:53:42.046Z","latestLabel":"6/10","dateHuman":"Jun 10, 2026","dateUpper":"JUN 10, 2026","dateFile":"Jun10_2026","rangeHuman":"Mar–Jun 10, 2026"}